The paper focuses on the design and management of networks for IoT, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of online learning algorithms for adaptive management of IoT networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the need for optimization and control in IoT networks, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of fog computing, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). Finally, the paper mentions the need for efficient communication in IoT networks, which falls under the category of information theory (cs.IT).
